%text Sometimes you will have to find the equation of a line given its slope, points it passes through etc And at other times, you will have to do the opposite You will be \underline\text{given the equation} of a line and you will have to figure out the line's slope, where it intersects with another line, it's $x-$ and $y-$ intercepts etc So, given a line $L_1: ax + by + c = 0$, re-write it as \[ \qquad y = -\frac{a}{b} x - \frac{c}{b}\]
% \begin{align} \begin{tabular}{cNN}
\hline & \text{Value} & \text{How?} \\ \hline Slope & m = -\frac{a}{b} & y = mx + c \\ \hline $x$-intercept & -\frac{c}{a} & \text{Put }y = 0 \\ \hline $y$-intercept & -\frac{c}{b} & \text{Put } x= 0 \\ \hline Point of intersection & & \text{Solve } y = m_1 x + c_1 \\ & & = m_2 x + c_2 \\ \hline \end{tabular} \end{align} %text %
